> Leek and potato soup is a classically Irish recipe that's creamy, comforting, and wonderfully warming. This particular dish is spiced up just a bit with the addition of a herby and smoky chorizo crumb.

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Thinly slice.

Chop the @potatoes{400%g} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Roughly chop half the @parsley{5%g} (double for 4p), stalks and all.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{to taste} in a large #pot{} (for the soup) on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the leek and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cook the leek until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Add the potatoes and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Sprinkle @flour{2%tbsp} (double for 4p) over the potato and leek. Mix together and
cook for ~{1%minute}, stirring frequently.

Add the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and @water{450%ml} (double for 4p). Bring to a
boil and simmer for ~{10-12%minutes}, or until the potatoes are tender.

Add the @creme fraiche{125%g}. Using a #blender{} or #food processor{}, blend the
mixture until smooth.

Add more water, in small increments, if you'd like your soup to be thinner.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

While the soup simmers heat a large pan on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once the pan is hot, add the @chorizo{100%g} and fry until it starts to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of oil (if required) and the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}. Fry for an
additional ~{1%minute}, until the crumbs are golden.

Remove from the heat and mix together with the chopped parsley.

Once the soup is almost ready, pop the @brioche buns{2} onto a #baking tray{}.

Warm through in the oven, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Dish up a hearty helping of potato and leek soup.

Top with the chorizo and parsley crumb and serve with a warmed brioche bun.